&lt;p&gt;Job Title&lt;br /&gt;Highly Specialised Cardiac Physiologist (Echocardiography)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Staff Group&lt;br /&gt;Healthcare Scientists&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band&lt;br /&gt;AFC Band 7&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours&lt;br /&gt;30 hrs per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal Enquiries to&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Andrea Stead, Manager of CRI&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Johnny Matthews, Echo Team Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cardio-respiratory investigations (CRI) unit is a busy diagnostics department in a modern and spacious setting within Tameside General Hospital. The service is undergoing an exciting transformation and we are looking for a motivated and experienced echocardiographer to be a part of the exciting developments ahead.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department performs approximately 8, 000 transthoracic echocardiograms (TTE) per year plus transoesophageal (TOE), contrast echo and an evolving physiologist-lead stress echo service. In line with our Trust’s ‘integrated’ status community-based diagnostic services are also currently under development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A cardiac physiology degree or equivalent, full BSE accreditation and post accreditation experience are all essential for this post. Competency within other cardio-respiratory modalities would be an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ongoing CPD is encouraged and development of new and existing skills will be supported whenever possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Andrea Stead - CRI manager&lt;br /&gt;andrea.stead@tgh.nhs.uk 0161 922 6314&lt;/p&gt;
